0JzLrQ3908wogRNl6H893OESHGNEIV=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-24"},{"Name":"Govinda Tamburino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXokIjfBoapji_v2smbg5VvxwbNHPoXZg4JY-XVPMU5wKyz4tOj=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After reaching out to three other HVAC companies—Lifetime Heating and A/C, Go Green, and Evergreen—I ultimately chose Ballard Natural Gas to install a new Mitsubishi HyperHeat heat pump in my home.\n\nJoe, the sales person, truly earns his title as a systems design expert. He was the only one who took the time to thoroughly calculate my home's manual J, measuring every window and coming prepared with the King County property record to ensure accurate sizing. This attention to detail immediately set Ballard apart. Joe explained every step of the process, which gave me confidence in the project, especially compared to the other companies whose sales reps spent just five minutes looking around before leaving. Ballard provided the most reasonable quote and was flexible during negotiations\n\nThe entire Ballard team made the experience seamless. Zoe from finance was incredibly helpful, patiently walking me through all my financing options and even resolving a concern I had about Ballard’s warranty and lifetime service claims—both of which are solid and reassuring. Clinton also deserves a shoutout for confirming the work I needed to do to install the A/C disconnect for the outdoor unit; his enabling and helpful attitude made both my prep work and the installation day smooth and successful. On installation day, Jay and Anthony, the service technicians, were fantastic. They took great care to keep my home clean, and Anthony worked hard to ensure the outdoor unit was installed tightly and neatly. Jay’s nearly 30 years of experience showed in the fit and finish of the indoor unit—his work integrating it with my existing ductwork was truly impressive.\n\nOverall, I would easily recommend Ballard Natural Gas to anyone considering HVAC work. From the first touchpoint, every member of the team was professional, thorough, and genuinely invested in making sure the job was done right. The combination of expertise, attention to detail, and customer service made this a standout experience.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1eI4rV6_Lpl5pGISx6-W1ud4uaWn9j52Pc9HU-l0HWhE71BypGhy2g4cIf_DSZT51icgrJXJdBWgLsxxS9dwqvFmSfO-K8jWnFxsJPyaDrnatawOr5PTi6Qljqd-8_-UysxU7lJdYB9ve1=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3AfgG4r4IHsClBRqLBWfcfmNv_8QI5ydoGP9XLcKKUBWvhosgW0gXudKM4aSmWEyUTWLdPcyP6RfuNNU2CVeB2QH6JjNQ3ITaf_o38wbdUzfPgiMXcRcmgZ76J9t7N7i9SwITYR7HUUb9k=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-20"},{"Name":"Helen Halloran (Miss Hell'N)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWuIrrrotBLSLunul_y2TsQIslpzG1UdKbnO09BwGlgDYmxeN1g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ballard Natural Gas just completed the installation in our condo of mini splits. It took two days, and scheduling was super easy and prompt. I choose them because of all the vendors I had come out and provide estimates, they were the most thorough, explained everything well, and the price was reasonable. Tony came out to do the estimate, and Zoe helped with scheduling and figuring out the financial piece. Installation was done by Juan, Humberto, Alex \u0026 DJ, and they were very professional, polite, on time and easy to work with. I definitely recommend them.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn21IFRufLh8hhJQlUDV2GUkeY76df3pJDkkDRXcPdEItCIxF0BmLBa_QRCzV3vYWWWB9571LHt692JkSGA64GsTm6n66VEREL37W1s820GN_7LWDBi5KEvIQ9_0rjRGWL0pna_FHJ2j6xQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2h6gvPEP0zN46xTr_tfIqhsXSHcASJqNBM5m1SnP21eBK-eVUqsFLjb8I0f-yUxnc8tEQdsJLARt1DLxJx_RQBoCzR4zD2hRmpBq1HZS3O_NL449QtQlBzNsqRa0cEdfgsBOaQlgTlz7ob=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2y0ERus3F-L1POD9VW87MdJx1hkvlaJQ2H90xbCHD9AFz8Q51LMEpEWCLPmhxyJMkMqBLWha0R-w9_G_tSpXsYLqVAWe7OnsZlRBwHGbW__JmC0QrPlENKTbtWx7XwEozjbwotykkwRH-R=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1GuDI_B9SMDlkom-NIYdzihAfoXxwKcEULrExdnyk3qFTZGtyQYxovUceWwRQSzRHMyeK3_HeKrQZouHVJkJpZ9jgmHBiZBGrWYamHmySfHMuDIQb1L2aLlxlRA1nPlnlvvlybLE-SXJEA=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2864ZguQ2-YQJ-yFRUyIgZczQbK-BL2cdVStiQhua3HymYoMXX_sUytVTfoQH2JrnBzfe6jL9TjqnrLHSlY0rXyql9t09NgNvfMIX-R5FUD2O4Y0ifWSkASaST5WS3Yz4t-4E7ErgoK1eY=k-no"],"When":"2025-8-29"},{"Name":"Lynne Russell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJoCTzyJqHJCBAzqBYX2XKnMZB7iBd3RHYfRyc52mPriudEzQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a new furnace and 2 splits installed today and it couldn’t have went more smoothly.  I was a little nervous about the job, but Jay, Anthony, Nick and electrician D.J. were all wonderful to work with and very knowledgeable and confident in their skills.  They even found a less intrusive way to do part of the job that worked out great.  Very nice crew, and Ashley and Zoe and the rest of office staff are equally friendly and very responsive.  Been a costumer for years for repairs and maintenance, and with this first major purchase would definitely continue to recommend them - great company.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Constantin Erens","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIi1hhAQiLXPLNS-EonjIQVtMNQMpK2DXbpd9Pi8iqXzf7r1w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"​I initially called Ballard Natural Gas Service because my old furnace was making a high-pitched noise. The technician was thorough and knowledgeable, explaining the issues and my repair options in great detail. I already suspected the unit was on its last legs, and while he confirmed that, he still provided a full itemized quote for the repairs that same day.\n​I decided to look into a total replacement instead, and their design expert, Tyler, came out that very afternoon. I opted for a heat pump and a new tankless water heater. It was a custom solution that involved reusing some existing ductwork while adding two new zones with mini-splits.\n​The installers, Brady and Cody, did a fantastic job. They worked efficiently, always used floor and furniture protection, and cleaned up thoroughly. They even stayed late on the final day to ensure the job was finished, only leaving once they were sure I was happy and had no remaining questions. They were also a pleasure to chat with—happy to explain the technical side of the job or share a bit about themselves. (Did you know Brady has 8 pet tarantulas?!)\n​Overall, I’m extremely happy with the new system and the entire experience. I wasn't expecting to do this much work when I first called, and while it was a significant investment, I never felt upsold. They were completely transparent with their pricing and the reasoning behind the system design. I truly feel I got a great deal considering the quality of the equipment and the professional workmanship.\n​Hot tip: Replace your furnace in March—it’s cheaper! 😬","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Danielle G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcuhLqDAgvvszOlNqtWoluHZ2JkIECPHUd-ZusJEeqc7aMgIog=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We knew our tankless gas hot water heater was on its last legs; it ran into errors all the time leaving us with no hot water frequently, and it was LOUD.\n\nI got a fast, very reasonable quote from Tyler at Ballard Natural Gas Service. The quote that he sent me was thorough, but he still made time to discuss the nuts and bolts over the phone. I really appreciated that he answered so many of my questions and really put my mind at ease - we got conflicting quotes and ideas from other plumbers, but Tyler talked me through the logistics, codes, and everything we'd need to consider when selecting a replacement. He seemed really trustworthy from the jump. I also appreciated that BNGS is local, and has been in business for 30+ years.\n\nAfter agreeing to their quote, I worked with Project Coordinator Zoe who helped us book the installation, and discussed financing options with me. She was also super thorough and lightning fast.\n\nAnd finally, our installer Jay showed up on time and replaced our unit with an upgraded version. He was super fast and efficient, and answered my questions before he left. He made sure to lay down tarps to keep our space clean, and his workmanship was wonderful.\n\nIt's been a few days with our new unit and it's been quite cold at night... and I wish we had done this upgrade sooner! Ballard Natural Gas made it a smooth and fast experience, and their quote was very reasonable compared to other businesses in Seattle. If you need tankless system maintenance or replacements, I'd recommend BNGS!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"andy wright","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIpe4sYiZZr9LYql2RG96J9vvkqwIk4cAxpnxj4XJjlJ95fD0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been in Seattle long enough to try several different HVAC service companies and this one is the best. I have used them several times. Never any high-pressure selling. I trust them when they say something is broken and needs to be replaced. Austin did a fair and thorough diagnostic visit. Jay and Anthony were very friendly and did an amazing install job. The new furnace install looks a lot better than the previous one.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3zSH0JGlTQ_EFm8AKDfCx2Cee9YNkfKIUQOrUHCNUY3ehElnfXXV9gDnGjTrUx4yeipqCFqheVae2LdsOm6feKGf-gFOMa49xTG_4l7PPyCXG12-C3TRyaGRVukjZgiiJt1MmEhzo949A=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-15"},{"Name":"Virginia Viehmann","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIpIFloLFqu1AywwZsAqu8bZahGhuigUqvfCVG5F59fkjUL5w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We recently hired Ballard Natural Gas to install a new HVAC system including all the ducting and vents in our new but old home in Olympia area.  From start to finish BNG were wonderful and we are very happy with the outcome and the constant heat throughout our house.   The initial consultant/salesperson, Tony, was very helpful, showed us how the whole process would go and gave us a very good estimate.  Zoe and Caliegh, worked to get the admin \u0026 permits, they were very responsive and helpful.  The entire crew from Clinton, the project manager, DJ the Electrician, and especially the two install technicians, Brady and Cole they did an awesome job.  Brady and Cole were here for 4 days and they were on time, worked very hard, knew what they were doing and cleaned up every day before they left.  All the permits have been signed off and both inspectors said that they did a very profession install with quality work.  Thank you BNG for a great job!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
