ddress":{"borough":"","street":"8731 Maltby Rd # 11","city":"Snohomish","postal_code":"98296","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":null,"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Casey Martin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJc0ctKReI-kAJt5F0HKPwoldvoEkgAEUdVLUXIOr2bZ5CGQg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As a general contractor, I have had the pleasure of working with numerous subcontractors, and I must say that Pop Electric, led by owner Darren, stands out as a shining example of excellence in the electrical services industry.\n\nPop Electric has consistently delivered top-notch quality work on every project we've collaborated on. Their attention to detail, precision in execution, and commitment to meeting and exceeding industry standards are truly commendable. It's evident that Pop Electric takes pride in their craftsmanship, and this dedication to quality has significantly contributed to the success of the projects we've worked on together.\n\nBeyond the exceptional workmanship, Pop Electric consistently provides outstanding customer service. Communication is key in the construction industry, and Pop Electric excels in keeping the lines of communication open, transparent, and effective. Their team is responsive, proactive, and always willing to go the extra mile to address any concerns or questions promptly. This level of customer service has not only impressed me but has also contributed to a smooth and collaborative working relationship.\n\nIn an industry where pricing can often be a concern, Pop Electric has consistently demonstrated a commitment to fair and transparent pricing. Darren and his team provide accurate and reasonable estimates, ensuring that there are no surprises when it comes to the financial aspects of a project. This level of fairness and integrity in pricing is a rare find and speaks volumes about the ethical business practices upheld at Pop Electric.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jessica Kessler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUo8jo2ySQN69mLlVGuXHrNdKiaS9piuiahaBnBevzd_9WhC0UM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"My husband and I were interested in a home built in 1971 \u0026 of course it has aluminum wiring.  We were told to contact P.O.P electric for a copalum connector repair bid and spoke with Darren.  He came out \u0026 prepared a reasonable bid, which we used to reduce the price of the house \u0026 get our closing costs covered by the sellers.  We were very impressed by his knowledge and trusted that he would help make our house safe.  We confirmed over the phone that he would start work the week of August 31st.  The week before I emailed with no response \u0026 left a voice mail message to confirm that we were all set to go, no response.  I called Monday morning and received a text that he couldn't start today and would call me later in the morning.  He never called.  Next day my husband got on the phone Darren eventually \u0026 Darren said his guy never works on Monday \u0026 was all tied up, but would try to get him out by the end of the week.  He said he'd update us the following day.  He never called us back and then stopped answering our calls \u0026 emailed.  Darren GHOSTED us!!!  GHOSTED us!!  I grown man stopped picking up the phone to avoid conflict and left us hanging out to dry.  We have to pay an extra month in rent because of the set up. Luckily we found another company that can do the Alumiconn connectors instead.  Darren is the worst!  Don't use this company","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGxYN0x21zV9U_pfz3R-ZseEG5-LGKUH_a5O2ISHIE-pMvTA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Update (2018.11): I had a warranty item come up recently and Pop Electric followed up and communicated in a timely manner which was appreciated. Thank you.\n\nOriginal Post: We have aluminum wiring and Pop electric is the only outfit in the state that does Copalum crimps which is why we decided to go with them (there is another crimping option which is bulky that other outfits offer but this is what we opted for). Aside from the Copalum crimps, we had them swap out fixtures, add can lights, switches and rewire for the kitchen. While their installer was good to work with and communicated well that cannot be said for their estimator/owner. There were numerous times that I tried to contact the estimator (who is the owner) via phone (office \u0026 cell) and email for some additional pricing or questions or to get update on where things sit and I might as well have  been talking to a black hole as there was little to ZERO followup on their end - VERY FRUSTRATING.  Billing was a joke, took about 90 days to get our bill after being told we'd have it sooner, very little detail - lump sum, didn't appear that they applied any of the unit pricing from their estimate; we paid and will utilize a different electrician for our future electrical needs. If you have aluminum wiring, you might be stuck with Pop \u0026 the Copalum crimps but you have other options for the rest of your electrical needs!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Scott Omli (JoeHair)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWwjimi0RGdR6sBQh1ufRprsfEkOnTrQZm9WzaWphuC1pJZSr1nKA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Although they never returned my call (that I know of), I would still recommend them to anyone for their many years as both electrical contractors and /or long time family friends and subcontractors. 3 + Generations of electrical experience in the north end of Seattle area and Snohomish County.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joey Perrigo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJWRQ5S3095oL2mp1gNnyMSUMG1gepWbvHyb137PPxC5VJ00g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Have recommended POP electric for over 25 years. They not only do a great job but they are an honest company. You can trust them.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bonnie Riley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkUynO386ErPiq6LXY0yLKBN2Untqd6QZece57qGGZMkhtfPvy=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Unprofessional, just will stop responding and give no reason leaving you in a bind.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mary Husby","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVOrT3qIKfhCcoZBjQu9rA2uarXGhwYSI-z8JuSaDQGhSXxAAkR=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very courteous and efficient","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jonathan Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzhfITgv-vfnDSMF3e9gFQH8U6RVebsj1Mka14c33zy-V1EyAD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
