ercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0N34h36AlTC_ZpTY1ZHPuDCImCmgU3XwBsZ5ZFZ27Kn7R8By41StPJ2kPClH4Z3yLBECQRjktMSyzZVXUSkjh2rFA5aoXRTr5pxvWiVd0P6f0WB8LGsI74P4CUcepB_zIxyOD6=k-no"],"When":"2025-5-15"},{"Name":"Buckholz Real Estate Team","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVoioTbgqK8RlGXIjYsZnvDGWACWL6-Vj1e9GNVXTKR_VjYicwk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fantastic work! I had West Seattle Electric swap out 20 light fixtures on a home I am selling. They were able to get there quickly, completed the job in 1 day and left the home spotless. Their employees were polite and professional.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"efer zamorano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWCXGQvibPxZsuk1sJi_6v_pSqasoA-T_ndu4tulLE7W-LNtSVSkg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ryan started by educating me on the safety concerns of my mid 1940s existing electrical equipment. Showed me the differences between the different levels of equipment. He was the third electrician I had come look at my home and everyone else gave me roughly the same price on mediocre equipment. He showed me the newest and safest service and breaker panels and I gotta say they look wonderful. I couldn’t be happier with the way that his crew treated my family And the level of respect they gave my neighbors. I wouldn’t recommend anyone more than Ryan and his team.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3OPhh6VkQ4Rd3R3GLld_oEJgrvef3yA0v524uCFejA4QKKUMGf8fLEu4exCvXTLojXQYfkvRy-TrdzRYRg3TrDPBy-zw2G6kc2hAJePrxV5XnJ-X5fA05K-ktqbg484-tZV5d9=k-no"],"When":"2025-5-29"},{"Name":"Darren Davis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTIpWwxi6O7FBe3xEK_btIez5PjDxMkMimKNlfnjPAr_trSZA9=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I loved working with West Seattle Electric on my DADU. They were fast, professional, and communicated really well as the project progressed. They finished the job ahead of schedule and under budget.  I could not have been happier with their work.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Blake Bryant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTRjSS7CKhEA9I4BKHrg-fJuSslJa8SsMMRtVsHtuO7Jk8m3qS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had 6 quotes/estimates for a service upgrade to 200A along with some smaller projects and the one I got from WSES was the most detailed while containing several options. With several of the other companies, I got hand-wavy answers to all my questions for why things might be needed, but not WSES. Everything was explained clearly and I walked away actually understanding the reasoning behind changes.\n\nLiving in an older house, I've come to expect many \"surprises\" and I knew that was a likely possibility with this project. WSES was the only option that called out some of the likely surprises they might find.\n\nThe crew was very professional, always on time, and answered all of my questions when I had them. I got frequent progress updates and power was provided while the power to my house was out.\n\nI could not recommend Ryan and his crew enough!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Wendi Roland","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUSGZmcUhJv_hut4YJdjY73ZXQhHRz9ETSp8FHZsNkJDT6vNyTD=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"West Seattle Electric did an amazing job installing my new Leviton Electrical Smart Panel, whole house surge protector, EV chargers for 2 cars, and swapping out all my electrical outlets in my home.  All devices are working properly with no issues.  His staff was professional and courteous.  I recommend installing a whole house surge protector as the solar flares zapped my brand new furnace electrical components and the fix was expensive.  Well worth the investment.  These days people have so many new digital devices such as shower controls it's a good idea to protect expensive equipment.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3qNkU0sRi0UF6qAmUd