nquiry at 5am, since I was losing my mind and couldn’t sleep trying to figure out why my wiring kept tripping the breaker, and they were able to come help me the very same day!\n\nI would highly recommend Daniel and Jacob from @SurgeElectricalLLC. I know there are some interesting reviews on yelp about service being bad and hidden pricing, but I definitely did not experience that. They were both very professional and the upfront pricing made me trust them even more. You are shown the price of the job before they do anything and you have to choose to either accept or decline their work. When I went to pay, after the work was finished, it was indeed the same price we agreed on in the beginning.\n\nThe price is moderate for electrical work, but every customer that needs help with the simpler issues like mine need to know that if you don’t want to pay someone to help you for whatever reason, you need to take an active approach to learn and understand it from the professionals that know how to do it properly. With Daniel and Jacob, I did just that and gained invaluable knowledge!\n\nWith the wiring of the Deako switches being different from your standard light switch wiring, Daniel and Jacob were able to explain the differences to me in layman’s terms with some jargon thrown in to learn the actual terminology so that I can feel confident about changing our other Deako single pole switches.\n\nIf you are new to electrical work and in need of light switch help like me, this was a FANTASTIC experience. What took me 5 hours to do, and fail at, Daniel and Jacob did in 10 minutes and were able to explain the differences of what I did versus how it should have actually been wired.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0_PHHrCqgjnuYKeDwMgiUNUH3ArKTj6O1P06xar895obgICqeTWj0OsMu_jLfUqsoEU9ha_7Q9-wdUmb69Wa_60wGZrb_mhSkn9-V5XUcC7y7qo67rQphNCYOE8gdCIeD4W6nx1aqwgrM=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-29"},{"Name":"Andrey Krasovskiy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercont