mFUhoPJ6CWTYPGtt_O6Ugre-og-2MbOlfsux1ycZc00dHd9Slojevu=w224-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=vQtmMKAUF9655rrjQY7dDQ\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=96.53744\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"112291348900387266144","name":"Brady Electric (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112291348900387266144"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Genesee","street":"4412 California Ave SW West","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98116","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":null,"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Kinsley Winn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUUOP36pLOs8zOT6Nyvm6vexhbVg2qsRdBrvm9GDBkG83aPv_hPGg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Michael helped us replace a corroded breaker and fix an ungrounded outlet. He was able to review our issues virtually before quoting us. He responded quickly to schedule time to come out to fix everything for us. He also recommended some things to do in the future to ensure our panel was in the best working condition.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lisa Markavage","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV8UdAwfMttaI8WcmceTBZ7cOi5xVP46KsicNezQumxLmHij6kWWQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Michael did a great job with some electrical items we needed fixed. His communication was great. It took him a bit longer than he expected, but he stuck to his quote which was really appreciated.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Matt Wenger","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwTsU56MetsOq6HfSLnRAELuCcK7XuDGinqMbgSe0oeDYTAeuvFg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Michael Brady was able to remove our wall heaters quickly in our townhome and convert a utility outlet into a regular outlet near the toilet for a bidet. Thanks for the help!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bill Griffith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXv4ROSEoiAcHQJHb2jW0V1d609GIG-9c3WWSL1sfip_AvI67tk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Michael went the extra mile so to speak in working an unusual electrical problem for me.\nHe’s personable and professional, comfortable with answering questions and chatting while he works.  And, he cleans up his mess!  His mother and father would be proud!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"David Skover","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKtWmBVUQehKLfVMYLYHqpv6igYgOuSIwB4dSyrlxFH8qDN_w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"West Seattle is very lucky to have its own local expert electrician!  Michael answered my call, came out one hour later on a weekend, courteously explained the situation and answered my questions, fixed my problem efficiently, and charged me a very reasonable price for a Saturday service!  I recommend Michael without hesitation.  He is now my new go-to for electrical issues!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shawn Findley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJQ2lviKSkY1alM2CzQykDBIIw7PpmRSbBS8aqeD6NwyBUzAw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great experience.  You can clearly tell Michael enjoys his job.  Got great vibes from the first time he picked up the phone.  Seemed truly interested in helping me figure out a solution to my problem and didn't talk to me like I was an idiot.  Michael is super comfortable to speak to and he involved me in the troubleshooting process (learned a ton!).  Will definitely use Michael again in the future for electrical needs!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jamie Briant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVU_dckpAfLHBTuZeJRWlS1FYfFkWktCtjzlhN6q5xTWa_uHEPZ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Michael did an amazing job when we lost power during the storm in November 2024. I've relied on him since to hook up an EV charger and add more sockets to our basement, and I highly recommend him.\n\nJust before thanksgiving 2024 we lost power, like almost everyone else in Seattle. Unlike everyone else, we still had no power five days later. I phoned a number I got on google, and they came to take a look. Our electrical panel appeared to have had long term water damage, to the extent our main breaker was so corroded it had fallen apart. These yahoos quoted me $18,000 to fix the problem, making all kinds of claims about \"code\" that turned out to be false. I said No Thank You. I was using a gasoline generator during the day to charge some big Jackery batteries, so we had the fridge working and the hot water pump, but no heat in the house. It got down to 48 degrees. When I realized my neighbors had power, one of them was kind enough to throw us an extension cable, but we still had no heat.\n\nI got Michael's number from a realtor friend, and after taking a look he quoted me a much more reasonable number. Michael does great work. I've seen the inside of our panel and it's very neat and tidy, not the birds nest that existed before he replaced it.\n\nMichael promised we'd have power for Thanksgiving, and true to his word he was here late on Wednesday night finishing the job. So many people were still having fallout from the storm, but Michael got us power back for Thanksgiving. That also meant we got heat back. We are thankful!\n\nMichael has since wired up a 60 amp circuit for an EV charger, so my car charges 10 times faster than before. He installed four new sockets in our basement, where I had previously been running far too much off a single socket, like you see in movies right before a fire.\n\nAll this work has been inspected and approved by the city.\n\nMichael got us out of the dark ages after the worst storm hit Seattle, without taking advantage of our situation, and with a super high quality of work. I have no hesitation recommending Michael.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"David Frost","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXukrpfz7J_qKSpx0cuEslwfy9D76FbeQFvHcDqwr5eyHKeSss6=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mike Brady of Brady Electric has helped us out on two occasions, most recently moving three 20A circuits from the back porch wood shop to my “new” inside wood shop location.\n\nHe got me on his schedule very quickly and accomplished the job with excellent quality in less time than I’d expected. He understood my requests, asked the right questions, and made sure the new circuits/outlets were where I wanted. Like any electrical technician of this high caliber, his work is not inexpensive, but I consider it good value, especially considering the following:\n\nI was really pleasantly surprised that he was able to make these changes so that no drywall repair was required afterward by cleverly using existing conduit and junction boxes outside my shop area. He anticipated how I’d likely need circuits in both locations while the shop is in transition. I hadn’t asked for that, but it has proved extremely helpful.\n\nHe is also great about following up to ensure that the job exceeded my expectations.\n\nI will certainly use Mike for future electrical work!","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
