s://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=EUm_OjV-E4OTHWh25ywX1g\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=14.507065\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://www.mirskyelectric.com/?utm_source=google\u0026utm_medium=organic\u0026utm_campaign=gmb_seattle","source":"mirskyelectric.com"}],"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"102135736760535193530","name":"Mirsky Electric (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102135736760535193530"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Ballard","street":"2442 NW Market St #599","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98107","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Online estimates","enabled":true},{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Andrew Diebag","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI_-rS5wqJF9ekhDLX4UYrm78_EE6z1-tZP2Nzn5_hb2inphA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely phenomenal work replacing our aging residential panel - the team was responsive, timely, and the fairest price I could find (and that’s after seven qoutes). If the have a bit of lead time - it’s well worth it for the fair, honest, and quality work product.\n\nHuge shoutout to my guy Seamus for getting us all hooked in!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3_s5nRGvNOMfz43FCFBQ-v3XV9nvFuBFQM5XMrij97Gcx-sdBfnfX2m9GTNPHd3GMlZgdPznyeg_CBxcPnYMysxZ4Hrk2l8LwMbZB-b6FtGT2yjWuwKC7GufKjZ1T3cIDDu0CIRQb7xtNr=k-no"],"When":"2026-2-4"},{"Name":"Michael Mann","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLcnqrot_FWvc66b60p3CZ4mj8itAT4nMEfbbHAwKUocRpBbQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"TOTALLY SOLD on Mirsky Electric! From beginning to end it was an exceptional experience. Adam was very professional, incredibly respectful of our property, and efficient/focused in getting the job done. Showed up precisely on time, and finished right on the bid-quoted estimate time.\nBig shout-out, too, for Gavin, the Service Manager! He is laser-focused on customer service and super easy to converse with answering questions, etc. These guys really go above/beyond in doing their utmost to make sure the customer has a flawless experience. I will not hesitate to utilize their services in the future; I won't bother looking for anyone else.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark H.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXlVEHlo3f7TyxXZkIZgDbfytBqUFplGxwFWfnTPeJcTAYIEd0u=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’m compelled to write this review for Mirsky Electric because we were impressed with their customer communication and technical skills.\nOur older home needed an electrical panel upgrade, and knob and tube wiring replacement. I searched for a local company because I wanted electricians with experience working with older Seattle homes. Mirsky fits those criteria. I also felt they put their customers, employees, and craftsmanship of the trade at highest priority.\nAt the beginning, Mike, the estimator, was very knowledgeable and a pleasure to work with. He supported me throughout the initial phase of the project, meeting with Seattle City Light representatives, and providing realistic cost estimates.\nOnce the rewiring phase began, it was a pleasure to watch the team work together. Grant, John, and Ross were efficient, communicative, and skilled in every aspect of the project. They were professional and took pride in their workmanship.\nAfter completion, I discovered that my doorbell no longer functioned. John returned the next day and made repairs to the wiring, including the installation of a new doorbell transformer.\nGavin, the service manager, was quick to answer emails, was flexible with our project’s start date, and kept me updated on the schedule. Both Grant and Gavin helped with cost estimates as things were added beyond the original estimate.\nNow we feel better about the safety of the electrical system in our home and have the capacity to add new systems such as an electric vehicle charger, heat pump, and other circuits for a possible future addition to the house.\nIn summary: no surprises, just good service. All anyone could ask for!\nP.S. I forgot to mention the efficient installation of our electric panel and relocation of the electric meter by Derek and Travis. We left the house for a few hours while the electricity was turned off. We returned and the box was in the wall the meter and wiring outside relocated, looking better than before!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rob Mathewson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXlhqAupEzsTUv5-RdCvuS77J4J3G-RIEax30-15qHbcehUmy55=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the second time that I've hired Mirsky and they've done great work each time. I had a list of issues to be investigated and Seth did a great job of diagnosing and then resolving them promptly. He explained some of the issues with my knob and tube wiring and was quite helpful.\nI'll be sure to have them back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chris Mills","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJkeq6krKducelC3eAlum3lJ_87eedNk2zbp7nx78Srd2k_pg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We will call them next time for sure, highly recommended. Arrived on time. Friendly and courteous, respectful of our house, and completed the work efficiently. In our case, that was replace three interior lights, replace three exterior outlets, and diagnose a broken bathroom fan. All done in less than two hours.\n\nThe fan problem turned out to be the motor which needed to be ordered, but they sent a link so I could order directly no markup, and showed me how to plug it in myself if I wanted to (no wiring involved) so I wouldn't have to pay for a return visit.\n\nIf every biz operated like this the world would be a better place.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Heide Sickles","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJfHNZ4C3Gik0q6oYAHiBCt4LJi3pOtIik0YPzoKjj8zz35dg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The dryer in our new house would not power on. My realtor recommended Mirsky Electric and I can see why. When I made an appointment for a technician come out and investigate Gaven identified the technician that was coming and had me send a photo of the electric panel so the technician would have any supplies needed for that. The technician, Seth, was great. He identified the problem immediately and, working in the tight confines of a very small laundry room, had it running in no time.  He even vacuumed the electric panel, which he did not have to do. I would use Mirsky again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michelle Hippe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0fb8kgudV2-e_o7Iqs_BuV9J8045dLInHLeI2_XQNYupJnAdMEg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Thanks Adam for being punctual, polite, efficient, and educational!  I swapped out lighting fixtures in my basement and inadvertently left a wire in 1 fixture loosely connected, so the connecting fixture did not have enough power and would not light. Adam quickly figured out the connection issue, and installed the other light. I asked about installing a tankless water heater down the road, and we were able to talk it through at the panel. Easy scheduling on the website, and friendly email confirmation before the visit. You guys have it down!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael Clark","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVI-vOcb-7N2LGQ5dHA8AfWJzkslXOedCfknDYPd_BmZsavgHd4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had an outstanding experience with Mirsky Electric and will recommend them highly to friends and colleagues. The gentleman who came to our home was knowledgeable, patient, and professional. Thank you again, team.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
