ox with a new 200-amp panel. The entire process took just two days—day one was prep work, and day two was installation with only about a 30-minute power outage. The electricians were professional, courteous, and took the time to answer all my questions. Everything went smoothly and seamlessly. Highly recommend!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0l2exttw0Pc56ChTbGUWWUVJJaoVvs1mtwXAM5MMwe1UrH_k8ot8W70LFSZOjDxS9JbXD8tUKc7zl0dt-1a821UzOCZRuNtHfuwr1C7pxR639XqszdUy_kbMrEfkZoRF1fhxlsh7b04vPN=k-no"],"When":"2025-9-25"},{"Name":"Alex Jiao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGh-o-gD8N9E-OaPUSFuus2q4wD3iClH5RnC1fqjJ5v63nFJEt2g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had Tyler from Economy Wiring install a fireplace, outlet, and a bathroom exhaust fan. He's been excellent - always on time, great communication, and as a person is very courteous, friendly, and professional. The price seemed very reasonable, he broke down the quote pricing by item (fireplace), and worked with our other contractor (fireplace surround) and coordinated with him to make sure our fireplace was installed and set up perfectly. Tyler was honestly great and I will definitely go back with him again the next time I need any electrical work done!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lissa Jagodnik","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXf2Lhjug1vEQx5K6DEjUysH9dWloklAq-07S667kZtaM7aj93C=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Economy Wiring replaced our ancient fuse box with a fully modern breaker box, including an exterior emergency shut off and an exterior outlet. Their employees were extremely courteous and respectful of our property. They did everything possible to minimize the need for drywall repairs, left VERY LITTLE mess, and even remembered to protect my dogs by closing the gate behind them, even if they were just going to their truck for a minute.  They were also very friendly and polite when asking for access to a closet or other space. They showed up on time, and worked efficiently and quickly. I was completely comfortable having them in my house and will call them again in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rose Ragan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIohOOVTSjtvMpe_bK3TsAJ2Nm2HXmTSqpzghAFHAhYrKztMA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had Economy Wiring come and install two new gas fireplace stoves.  They had to extend the gas piping and punch it through the wall.  They also had to cut through the wall in two places for the vent ducting.  The installation was great and very thorough.  All sealed, square, aligned and looking good!  Tyler and his helper (so sorry I forgot his name) were fast, courteous, always wearing their masks, and the clean up was excellent.  Pricing was super fair and Tyler spent extra time making sure I fully understood the fireplaces and how they should work.  I had purchased the new fireplaces somewhere else and had installed an aftermarket thermostat prior to them installing the fireplace and I had installed it incorrectly.  Tyler knew exactly what to do and didn't give me any grief about having to fix my error.  I'd say that he is a true salesman and has all the best qualities of customer service, repair technician, carpenter, electrician and gas piping plumber!  A new addition to Economy and a good one!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"C J “Panmondiale”","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzkrRb-9NFQqWphl5aGrhCr3b1q6hxULWh_KDtz4CwuqLzwyC0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have a Monessen gas fireplace, purchased from and installed by a local company, that was not working properly. Because the company that we purchased it from had proved its incompetence in both installing and servicing the unit, when it began to malfunction - turning off after as little as a few minutes - I wanted to find a repair service that was more competent and reliable. After calling a number of places and being told that “we only service what we sell,” “we don’t service that brand,” or, “we’re happy to help you, but our first available appointment is four months out,” I struck upon Economy Wiring and Tyler Tillman. Tyler was fantastic - he was able to successfully diagnose the problem and repair our fireplace and did it in a timely fashion. Although it took two trips (not his fault but mine) to get it to 100%, at no time did I question his ability to get the job done or his competence in doing so. If you have a need for a gas fireplace repair, I would highly recommend Economy Wiring. I’ve dealt with a lot of technicians and repair people over the years, and none of them were more capable than Tyler. And based on my experience, I have to believe that everyone at Economy Wiring is cut from that same rare cloth. Highly recommended.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paula Bachtold","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJMq1P26X-BH7wK8CBYEUnX-N_vMlsGW15PzQtMP_CKnOEphw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I called several heating and air establishments in need of a new furnace and air conditioning unit and Economy Wiring Company had the best offer by far.  Economy Wiring exceeded all expectations and did a fantastic job.  Workers were here on the job everyday they said they would be, very friendly, and did a very professional job.  Best of all I love my new furnace and look forward to using my air conditioner this summer.  Great experience all around!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Aaron Beck","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIcMBAJFueCN7kRrjkjc9huTPeadg1m-JnL1zVSuOczTkg-kw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have to say I was quite impressed with Economy Wiring after calling them to replace our electrical panel. They were the third quote I had received for the job and were the only company that I felt priced fairly. The first company quoted over $2000 higher!! Ed was 