ummer. Looking forward to the year round comfort, extra green in my pocket while doing my part for mankind. Lol!\n\nThe install team and electrician were very informative, skilled and surprisingly more quiet than expected. May not live in a palace, but they treated like one laying down floor covering and cleaning up after themselves.\n\nThank you Premier team","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2QPjnyY93D33k5RGZN5IBYztIGuVAuQ7gtUQwyklpdb0sdqJXTWBYQzxi9MpOGxsC8MEAkGfyeT496Zcj20ip-BesWz9rftvqpxbVkS8_6YzAihFkZP7A4rm6e1p8clJt9r6Ek=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3H53cKyvds_X3xFZceVlYr0Pi6r1NX4OITx_UN_fzRtkeik7qUG2NEpo3TXoKZFQhVUOlklpnkbCVMXcMiCY0V1HWs0Ce_48sbphSb1VA72cfpYvxVAHPNX7-7Wb7aUXYYy3R1=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1DUtGOOGtEgZ3KAjgHQpvmtunzY62l4TpMUOxxRw9Nsq18XDvMSn4irGDqO9DrCrpv-7S7L2FNoN5W_k38ZKVmGEDr2S2m0jRNgoYCHiEWZREQWCnSY-6C30r2sdj5A9jCOtZz2A=k-no"],"When":"2025-2-22"},{"Name":"Rex Hohlbein","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkL6z77z0DKfnHQrOHUG2388JPE5mBqEO5LrCGKBO0tApEA2W6=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As an architect with over 35 years of experience I've worked with Premier Mechanical \u0026 Electric for years and years. All of our clients have been greatly impressed with their up to the moment knowledge when going through the design process and equally satisfied with the workmanship and expertise of their crew from beginning to end of installation. I would highly recommend Premier Mechanical \u0026 Electric to anyone. This photo is the water heater in my own home that Premier installed! THANKS to all of the crew!!!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3B2prvp33QmfUF8XYlt4Pngqcf-ABt3CBMrDFGuNwpgkNDjyFqdjC-63_hg5oRmsnZAE_NzjRbIhjXgS0CZUbRFG6mY2ZfM96BygEzthyJQ1xYzxrmy-lUN8D9nyQ-xe9OC8bOOQ=k-no"],"When":"2022-3-7"},{"Name":"bchungate","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyhvDDComEqbU6WquBilLH6GZsXveDczKXK2vv_QWuz_2Q7kCg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Outstanding service from quote to installation to billing. We had a heat pump added to an existing furnace/ ductwork in an older home. These are real people who understand constraints of a situation and come up with viable, excellent solutions. All members of their team are personable and professional. So nice to deal with individuals who treat everyone, including pets, with kindness. We cannot express how happy we are with the work done for us.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"John VanRoekel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVF9slWIypd2_Titloz1tdabjgioFRCHJRXD0q2Rl0IHxdhszhb=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I called Premier when our heater conked out.  They had a Tech available within 24 hours.  He was prompt, super professional, and had the heat back on in about half an hour.  Truly great service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Robin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdMgp4EJz823Poat4bQexVLNPbxppjTHABOGV_OX-EsyVo4TGy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Called Premier Mechanical for a routine maintenance on water heater. I was told on the phone that the service, including flushing the water heater, would be $185 total.\n\nIn reality, it’s $185 for the first 30min of service... and then $75 for 30min extra, and flushing with chemicals is additional $50. Not what I was told at all.\n\nDuring the job, I did ask the technician for his thoughts on a super minor issue I noticed with the water heater, I appreciated his thoughts and willingness to fix it the right away. Now I understand why he started to fix it without telling me what the cost for me would be. Again if I had known originally the labor cost I would have never mentioned this issue, remember 30min = $75. When he insisted to spend another 20min on fixing the issue a different way, I did ask at that point \"what’s the cost to me\", he responded “just my time”, which I realized now was the vaguest response, I wish he had said “$75\" in which case I would have said “No thanks bye\".\n\nCommunication is part of your job, being vague and not upfront about your prices isn't how a good and honest business works. You lost a customer and earned a well deserved google review.\n\nI complained over email, nobody took any responsibility for what was communicated over the phone, I ended up paying a lot more than $185, and noticed next to my last name on the bill the mention \"DO NOT SERVICE\". It's ok, I added \"DO NOT HIRE\" next to your name in my contacts ;)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Todd Fiala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWXMjk791hZe0EW6jB_264XAdthviVoD3vM32UkpYofunZeQrIK=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Premier Mechanical \u0026 Electrical has done a whole slew of work in my home. They've redone in-floor radiant heating, added A/C throughout the house for a system that doesn't have vents, and also have done quite a bit of electrical work, including adding a natural-gas generator.  All their work has been high quality, top notch.  Very pleased.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Schuyler Lifschultz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0RFBTgSfvdP909KZTxRyEvScjl9-UGtJas8NDVLmfdNmkgUhKAA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"A service technician today was involved in a pretty severe road rage incident about 4:50 pm off Broadway and I-5. The technician was an absolute hot head \u0026q dangerous. It would be absurd to ever hire this firm for any of your mechanical or HVAC needs. Be safe out there, avoid these guys at all costs.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
