work with and extremely helpful. Would recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shayna Glazer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXcZ6eVmtwVU5q4cEMJtq-nP5grKPsHTND_pYsKvtX0XXyuzW3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Got a simple oil change, ready in a couple hours, easy in and out situation! The guys were nice and if I’m being honest, I think they vacuumed my front seats :))","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nene Nene Nene","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJeXE_RSfv-lDuWGKBNPHTDZuo8ANooVQxmLQlB9RH12j2FEg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"NEVER TRUST ACME! 🚫 It's a scam! I brought my car in for an AC check, and Curtis claimed they have found the issue under 25 minutes. However, after getting the \"repaired\" part replaced, I discovered they'd actually just loosened a wire and removed a fuse to make it seem like a bigger problem. As someone who works on their own vehicle, I knew all I needed was a simple AC charge/filled. Don't waste your hard-earned money on untrustworthy mechanics. Take your car elsewhere or save your funds and DIY (DO It Yourself) if you can. My problem been fixed I traveled to another state to refill my vehicle AC myself. I'll Never trust these people here ever again!! They want to charge an arm and a leg for something so simple to fix/do, but make it sound like it's a big issue to fix that's how these people make money by just having your vehicle sit in their shop for days and hours what a big SHAME 🫠","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joshua Merry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHoQ0OV02GjXyMSwjjqsSn5zkGAI66hHOuxeQHHqznv7zKWGgFRA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my first time taking my car to ACME.  My normal repair shop couldn't handle an electric fix.  They evaluated and identified the problem within a few hours.  Curtis drove over to Jeep to get the replacement part.  They fixed it that day, as well as fixing a few other problems, all for a reasonable price.  Five stars for speed, attention to detail, and solving a lot of small problems that have bothered me for a long time.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bob Jacobs","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJxyGR8nEi8SJANNAv1cutPHzaU8R-ZCiZceBOYDohnppu5YQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Curtis and Dan are simply the best.  I've been a car guy for decades, and I rarely see their combination of expertise, very fair pricing and superb customer service.  Was referred to Acme by my mechanic for a computer-related electrical problem.  Acme solved the problem quickly, fairly and with remarkable expertise.  The world of car repair needs more Acme!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Aishwarya Nair-Driscoll","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDMT3kagMJCkYLlzvxgzQaZpelsPXpMwwIelaZaFTGjxjPV9Q7=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"really great service, and nicer to know that i was supporting a small biz! i showed up 45 minutes before closing because i was concerned of a wiring issue with my headlights and the team took a quick look and immediately addressed the issue, going so far as driving up the street to find a replacement bulb. as they were wrapping up i asked about a potential brake issue and they took a look and gave me a rough estimate for what it would cost— such quick service and i’m looking forward to bringing my car back!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Philip Curry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2qrNqjRqBV0JchUed3g-UaG6lLHbYcgcPpbn0LXPkkStDCVgO=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great experience with Acme. Brought my 04 suburban here for various issues and they handled all of them well and efficiently.\nCurtis is a solid guy, very knowledgeable and transparent. Communication was prompt and accurate and courteous. He’s been at it 43 years, he knows what’s up!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name"