36107634820","name":"Ballard Electric Co (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108577060036107634820"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Queen Anne","street":"1080 W Ewing St Bldg D","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98119","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Debit cards","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"levSerd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUvqyFYclnf2tbrTVqr_JSylBd-gM35azKiSH5_nDODFgfFw0tf=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Was on my way to Ballard Electronics to pick up a starter when my outboard’s prop pin snapped. Jim didn’t hesitate — he jumped right in and helped me get it sorted even though that’s not what I came for. Total pro, knows his craft, and just a genuine guy with real heart. The starter service was great too. Big thanks to Jim and Ballard Electronics — people like that keep you moving.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jack Phillips","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUgqj_XUgbcoU1T4qoQCmZn1_OJmz5649qdlFZibpbUHfzID7UN=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"5 star, Jim is the man! I am rebuilding my starter, and I came in with some questions and to order some parts. He was knowledgeable and very helpful for what I needed. He is a cool reserved guy I think; easy to talk to.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Scott Bostrom","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIgU8gO07EuR2Z3pb2gL83HdAgwMTiUUd49_gPDXeIDhvS4Rg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was having a regulator issue on my alternator, and was pointed here.  Was told he was about a month out for work.  Walked in and talked to Jim. He gabed with me for a min, and grabbed my alternator and threw it on the bench. A new regulator and an enjoyable conversation later, I was off for a weekend sail on the boat I thought wasn't happening.  Recommend this place.  Thanks Jim.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Christian Jones","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK1UXDpepCCJS3o39VV20Q0NHU-49Vn0i6mqhe_n4Z1sI1xSg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This guy Jim has no clue what he's doing. I called and drove across Seattle after discussing the starter I needed and the job could be done that day. No problem. Left work only to get there and Jim told me they don't even have that stocked from here to Kansas City. He remembered the call and shrugged his shoulders. \"Sorry\" was his reply. I left work a half day early and he couldn't care less about it. He promptly went back to a conversation with his buddy.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Derek Storm","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocImUgW22mlLuwCDkdyl5roASuLwH5Mk84pniQq2Xv3N9qekOQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First of all, beware that they have moved from NW 49th St to 1080 W. Ewing St.  It is worth hunting for the place.  The shop is affiliated with Romaine electric in Kent.  We got a replacement, rebuilt starter for our boat from them a few years ago.  The solenoid failed during a cruise, and we sailed back assuming our cruise was over.  I took the starter to Jim at noon Friday.  He located a replacement solenoid somewhere on his delivery man's route, called the man, who could bring the part by 3:15.  Jim had the starter repaired by 3:30 and we were able to reinstall it and resume our cruise.   This is real service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"christopher ayala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGLuppL1-GXUkAZwFc8_eM0bURxFyloknd8CMaZEPF3SnAwgg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"JIM WAS ABSOLUTELY GREAT! HE HELPED ME WITH AN ALTERNATOR THAT WAS TOTALLY BURNED UP, AND HELP ME GET ONE THE WOULD WORK FOR MY VESSEL. GREAT GUY GREAT SERVICE. THANK YOU,  CHRIS","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Barbara Bennett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVRcAsWrEwCyEUAO3u-iKyFE0VPSSEyVix8iTHMC1lWB7zxMGnf=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We called from our boat and Jim answered. We gave our specs and he said he would check and call us back. He did within 5 mins. He had what we needed. He was willing to give complex directions instead of just saying google it. Went to pick up and was in and out within 5 minutes. Very friendly and helpful","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Scott Anderson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_RgmjouO7mfFnLJBh5GP0dhvkQkagA7wujlPouGXABXOQWQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Seeing the other great reviews, I usually would ignore a bad one like this. Someone can always find something wrong even when everyone else says great so go with the majority... But I urge you not to ignore this one. My rebuild was a vintage 6volt fan motor for a heater blower. It's a vintage 1941 car part so as I've done for many years with old car things, I clearly asked if this was something they even wanted to work on and the answer was yes. And I'm realistic that a small individual job will take a back seat to a big job, it's just good business. But it was pulling teeth to get them to even start on it. So finally it was done the first time, after waiting a couple of months, and they agreed it it didn't work right. Also, a hole was drilled in the bottom of the metal housing for which they had no explanation. So, after they agreed it needed to be further worked, it just sat on the shelf. Every time I asked it was \"not yet\"...and the reason was \"we just haven't gotten to it\". And each time it was the same guy mentioned in the other review(s). So I told them I'd be down the following Friday to pick it up done or not and lo and behold it was magically done. No explanation. So - just save yourself the frustration and months of time and go elsewhere.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
